  <text>At a duly called Session of the Legislature of the Kiowa Tribe held this 9th day of March, 2019, the following Resolution and Law were adopted.</text>
  <recitals>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS;</conjunction>
      <text> 	The Legislature is vested with the authority to pass laws and resolutions pursuant to <cite doc="Constitution of the Kiowa Tribe">Article VI, Section 6(a) of the Constitution of the Kiowa Tribe</cite>; and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS;</conjunction>
      <text> 	A RAP shall be developed and implemented by the Kiowa Tribe in funding year 2019, pursuant to the <cite doc="Constitution of the Kiowa Tribe">Kiowa Tribe Constitution - ARTICLE 6, Section 6</cite>, Powers (G); and,</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>WHEREAS;</conjunction>
      <text> 	A RAP is necessary to identify the distribution of Kiowa Casino revenue and for approval by the Bureau of Indian Affairs.</text>
    </recital>
    <recital>
      <conjunction>NOW THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED;</conjunction>
      <text> that the Legislature hereby enacts attached law entitled Resource Allocation Plan (RAP) Establishment Act of 2019..</text>
    </recital>
  </recitals>
